issue.title: Neutronium implementation
issue.body:
This PR adds a new application in the ReactiveTrader thread. Is uses [Neutronium](https://github.com/NeutroniumCore/Neutronium) as an UI framework that allows to use HTML technology for C# application. As neutronium is based on reactive principes on the top of MVVM, it was particularly well suited to integrate with ReactiveTrader. I found it might be a good idea to integrate this aplication in the main project, I would like to hear your feedback.

Tecnhically this PR contains contains:
-For the whole solution: an update of the nuget dependencies Fody and Reactive extension and the correction of the corresponding breaking changes.
-the addition of an Neutrion WPF application as a new project.

ObserveLatestOn cancels previous scheduled notification
issue.body:
`ObserveLatestOn` should not process previous items that were scheduled if a new notification arrives. This PR corrects the usage of `MultipleAssignmentDisposable` to using the `SerialDisposable`.

This was identified at YOW when reviewing the Histogram reports, however must have forgot to submit the changes we demoed onstage.
